10: I am ready whenever you are!
15:
To five elements—
Six companions new converge—
Countless paths laid bare.
19:
My, my! You've integrated our
elemental system into your own...
You really are an intriguing one!
24:
For a simple separation barrier, it's
rather basic. Stay just like that for
now, Inaho.
29:
I'm sure Yuki will be pleased to hear
she doesn't have to do ALL the
barrier-making from now on.
33:
Our real problem is the defensive
line. We'll have a real struggle on our
hands if we stay here.
37:
Then why not hide in the
Kaleidoscope? At least we'd have
the option of fleeing to another
world.
41:
That's an absolute last resort. If we
abandon this location, we'll lose any
hope of staging a proper
counterattack.
44:
Given how many people from
different worlds have gathered here,
I'm certain aid will come. We must
finish the evacuation and hold the
line.
56:
What's that?! Mr. Takamori's headed
to Shibuya as well?!
61:
I have a report from Memram
saying that those things have
appeared in Shibuya too! They're
chasing after the people who fled...
65:
...That's not good. Shibuya's skies are
wide open—practically begging to
be invaded.
69:
What about the underground? It
should be connected to the
Kaleidoscope—perhaps they can
use that as an escape route?
73:
There's just one problem... It's only
connected to the depths. You really
want ordinary people wandering
around there—where THOSE things
are running amok?
78:
We'll need a diversion if we're going
above ground. Gotta drag their
attention away somehow.
81:
Can't do it, little missy. Don't care
how much of a genius you are, your
body still has limits. Rest up.
90: I shall be the one to take on this task!
99: I... will do battle with those creatures!
102:
Th-that will not do, Lady Orvelle! As
a saint, you cannot put yourself at
such a risk!
104:
Besides... Are these beings
themselves not servants of the
Stars?!
106:
If that is the case... then perhaps the
Stars have forsaken us?
109:
Fret not. The Stars would never do
such a thing.
112:
The guidance of the Stars is with us
still. When the light fades, it is up to
us to extend a guiding hand to
those who have lost their way.
115:
After all, the people are calling upon
the Stars in prayer—they beg to see
the light of tomorrow!
125:
Well, now... Despite knowing the
truth—that your beliefs are nothing
but hollow fiction—
128:
...You would still have them think
that there is meaning in prayer?
132:
Of course. I've decided to be more
proactive about my goals—to kick
things into gear, so to speak.
136:
The truth is that I have been waging
my own battle for quite some time.
143:
Say... Can you connect different
portions of the Kaleidoscope
together?
146:
Um, I w-was thinking you could use
those shifts to make a sort of
shortcut through the Kaleidoscope...
151:
You did it with Yumu before, right?
And when Memram was trying to
help the Vesta.
158:
Not at all. You already have the
power—and the will—to see it done,
after all.
163:
That settles it! This darling girl shall
create the path using a shift... with
our assistance, naturally!
168:
All the more reason to create a
diversion. Keira, contact Memram's
group and have them head
underground!
178:
*pant* ...Just how long must I keep
this up?
182:
Is everyone in place? Lady Orvelle
will be taking point, so be sure to
keep your distance!
186:
All right, Guild Knights. No
slacking—don't want them
adventurers to show us up, now do
we?
189:
...Looks like we're all set. Spotlight's
all yours when you're ready to start
the show.
196: I seek to battle alongside you!
220:
Break time's over... Time to get to
work!
